 <H1>Conflict Serializability & Graphs</H1> 
 <P><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Theorem: A schedule is conflict serializable iff its precedence graph is acyclic.
</H2></P>

<P></UL><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Theorem: 2PL ensures that the precedence graph will be acyclic! 
</H2></P>

<P></UL><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Strict 2PL improves on this by avoiding cascading aborts, problems with undoing WW conflicts; i.e., ensuring recoverable schedules.</H2></P>

<P></UL></P>

